         <p class="- topic/p ">A manual bypass
switch is used to isolate sections for maintenance while supplying
the load from the bypass mains. A 3-position manual bypass switch
have the positions: <sl class="- topic/sl ">
               <sli class="- topic/sli ">In <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position the system can automatically switch between
normal operation and bypass operation without interruption.</sli>
               <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test </b> position is used to isolate sections for maintenances
or troubleshooting.</sli>
               <sli class="- topic/sli ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position is used to test the function of the
static switch EN or troubleshoot the system.</sli>
            </sl>
         </p>
      </div>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The static switch EN makes it possible to switch over to bypass
operation automatically without interruption.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The static switch EA is used to help isolate the system in bypass
operation, so there is no feedback from the static bypass to the inverter.
It also makes the switch between the inverter and bypass more controlled.</p>
